<raw><![CDATA[ (Updates to add Gibbs quote) WASHINGTON, April 23 (Reuters) - The White House said onFriday it backed Greece's decision to ask for the activation ofan EU/IMF aid package aimed at pulling the euro zone member outof a debt crisis. "We support that call for the activation," White Housespokesman Robert Gibbs told reporters. The U.S. Treasury Department was closely monitoring theGreek debt situation, he added. (Reporting by Matt Spetalnick; Editing by Will Dunham)             ]]></raw>
